reviews.title: Tonight
reviews.text:
It was super good again, my husband had the Cajun pancake and I had the salmon with pesto.
Nice and quiet during dinner.
We wanted to have dessert but this didn't work out for us, people arrived with a screaming baby and nagging children and here was not corrected by the parents on the so we found this very annoying and went away.
Very unfortunate that selfish behavior.
I understand that the pancake house is also meant for children but it is so nice when other people are also taken into account.

reviews.title: Dutch Pancakes
reviews.text: Local Dutch food. Unique experience of sweet and salty Dutch pancakes. My pancake came with bacon, sausage, mushrooms and egg. Try them.

reviews.title: Pancake house
reviews.text: Eating pancakes quickly. You can do that here, the children find it super tasty and fun and it is affordable and has plenty of choice.

reviews.title: Glass in my pancake
reviews.text:
Very bad service. There was glass in my pancake, yes real glass. I took the pieces out of my mouth and showed them to the waiter. I already received a strange reaction to this and I had to indicate that I wanted a new one. This took a very long time, so the rest of my party had finished all the food and I didn't need it anymore. The owner did not come to say sorry or anything like that afterwards. She just said she didn't understand where it came from.
When paying, the girl at the counter asked if she should remove the pancake, as it contained glass. No, absolutely not, the owner shouted, they just have to pay for it.

All in all a very bad restaurant, service is bad, everyone is crammed into the table so there is barely room to eat and it doesn't feel like they really enjoyed having you there.

reviews.title: Greatest Pannekoek in Twente
reviews.text: We have been coming to Twente, Holland for many years now and it has become a most to drop by minimum a couple of times for some pancakes at The Pannekoekhuis, great food, friendly service and family ambiance. Greatly recommended.

reviews.title: nice place to go with the family!
reviews.text: a large menu, so good choice of different pancakes, try something different! nice indoors, and when the weather is nice, also nice terrace! have fun!

Berlin is nothing if not resilient, having outlasted many turbulent periods in its history. Those scars still show today in the stark distinction felt between the east and west sides of the city even though it’s been decades since the Berlin Wall came down. And for a European capital city, it’s not conventionally beautiful like Paris or London. Instead, Berlin embraces its eccentric hodgepodge of grit and glamour.

It’s easy to get sidetracked in Krakow. I was expecting my first trip there to be all about the architecture—this is the city where its dazzling main square is ringed by buildings dating back to the Middle Ages, after all—but then I ducked into a little café on a nearby street. I got distracted by a platter of some of the best pierogies I’d ever had in my life. Suddenly history took a backseat to dumplings. Luckily there’s plenty of time for both, as you’ll see in the itinerary below.
